{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1774410472,"nonce":"JiEnXDTYy4T70tOdnnAcEvjpmA0=","message":"**Task design decision: constant reach length 0.5, center-out**\n\nWith translation invariance enforced (Bug: be3804f), all reaches become center-out from origin. Reach length fixed at 0.5 units (already the eval standard in task config).\n\nPhysics check: damping=10, mass=1, dt=0.01, ~80 movement timesteps. Peak velocity for 0.5-unit reach ≈ 1.25 units/s (bell-shaped profile). Well within operating range, not trivial, not saturating.\n\nConstant length chosen over variable because:\n1. Eliminates a confound when detecting SISU-conditional velocity modulation (\u003c1% so far)\n2. Adversary's problem is stationary across trials (only varies with direction and SISU), producing cleaner min-max equilibrium\n3. Variable length makes adversary jointly learn perturbation strategy as function of (length, SISU, phase) — slower convergence, harder to interpret\n\nVariable length is a valid generalization test for later, once the mechanism is demonstrated under controlled conditions.","files":null}]}